				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">And while we're on the topic, gamma is not an unwanted side-effect; it's a deliberate scheme for encoding luminance into an electrical/digital signal suited for human eyes' greater sensitivity to variations in luminance in the darker end than in the lighter end. A linear encoding would waste accuracy in the light tones and bring out more noise/quantization effects in the darker tones.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

