				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The 2.odd gamma characteristic was a fortunate side-effect of the roughly quadratic response of CRT kinescopes. The picture signal represents voltage, but light emission is roughly proportional to beam power, which in turn is proportional to the square of voltage: P = I²R = V²/R.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

